# NPPES ingest works by streaming (curl | bsdtar | node) — nothing lands on
# disk. This guards any future disk-based extraction from being committed.
.nppes-scratch/

# Payer-network harvest scratch — probe logs, samples, ad-hoc status scripts.
.harvest/

# Local design critiques (impeccable skill) — keep out of git
.impeccable/

# The impeccable skill itself — used occasionally, 2.2M/96 files, too heavy for
# the repo. Kept on local disk (still fully functional), just untracked.
.claude/skills/impeccable/

# Agent scratch dirs — may transiently hold pulled env values; never commit
.*-tmp/

# Stripe's official Connect sample app (downloaded 2026-07-20 as reference while
# building the marketplace). Third-party code with its OWN package.json and a
# .env file — tracking it would confuse tooling and normalise committing .env
# shapes into the repo, on the same night a key leaked (NYS-184). The patterns
# we took from it live in our own routes and docs/reference/stripe-connect-digest.md.
stripe-sample-code/
